Some of my `fixes` are really crazy (probably no one would even want to waste time for that), for example:<br />* Fixing broken (blob) CHR-ROM memory:<br /><a href="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/7455523800_1513255201.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/7455523800_1513255201_thumb.jpg" alt="Image" /></a> <br />* Fixing broken (blob) mapper chip (MMC1):<br /><a href="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/3092750000_1513255239.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/3092750000_1513255239_thumb.jpg" alt="Image" /></a> <br />* Fixing broken (blob) CHR-RAM:<br /><a href="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/4281527100_1513255384.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/4281527100_1513255384_thumb.jpg" alt="Image" /></a> <br />* Fixing broken PAL chip -&gt; replacing with Xilinx CPLD (version 1)<br /><a href="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/1112924700_1513255429.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/1112924700_1513255429_thumb.jpg" alt="Image" /></a> <br />* Same but with Altera CPLD:<br /><a href="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/1584608300_1513255474.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/1584608300_1513255474_thumb.jpg" alt="Image" /></a> <br />* This one consisted of 2x 8 MBit memory, which had single data bus pins broken -&gt; instead of replacing them, I just installed one memory that fixed data for the broken pins:<br /><a href="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/4507336800_1513255622.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/4507336800_1513255622_thumb.jpg" alt="Image" /></a> <br />* Broken ASIC BF9096 in Codemaster cart -&gt; fix with CPLD:<br /><a href="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/4130699400_1513255885.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/4130699400_1513255885_thumb.jpg" alt="Image" /></a> <br />* MMC3 chip had broken IRQ line -&gt; I had to implement this on cpld:<br /><a href="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/2939191500_1513257142.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/2939191500_1513257142_thumb.jpg" alt="Image" /></a> <br />*JY-120 (45 in 1): Some upper PRG/CHR lines of glob-mapper were broken but also reading PRG-ROM returns non consistent results<br /><a href="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/3121261300_1531934995.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/3121261300_1531934995_thumb.jpeg" alt="Image" /></a> <br />*Wario Land: CHR-ROM was broken, but instead of soldering 32 wires, soldered add-on board:<br /><a href="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/5203983200_1527008652.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/5203983200_1527008652_thumb.jpeg" alt="Image" /></a> <br />*Dragon Ball: Mapper chip was broken, but I was curious how to read PRG/CHR roms, so I soldered add-on board with latch:<br /><a href="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/4894718200_1531935245.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/4894718200_1531935245_thumb.jpeg" alt="Image" /></a> <br /><br />Some more ROM fixes:<br /><a href="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/5943906900_1531935454.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/5943906900_1531935454_thumb.jpeg" alt="Image" /></a> <br /><a href="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/1559873500_1531935777.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/1559873500_1531935777_thumb.jpeg" alt="Image" /></a> <a href="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/3376383300_1531935779.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="https://obrazki.elektroda.pl/3376383300_1531935779_thumb.jpeg" alt="Image" /></a><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4898">krzysiobal</a> â€” Wed Jul 18, 2018 10:27 am</p><hr />
